sentences.text:
The only substantive material which it could have contained was that:


 (1) Mr Goo had been described on the website of DSP as 'production manager' and this could be used to suggest that: 




 &#8226; the business takes orders in Australia; products from Korea are shipped to DSP and DSP does further work or tests on them in a factory and then sells them to the Australian business;
 &#8226; Mr Goo's income is derived from DSP; 




 (2) therefore Mr Goo is involved in the actual supply or direct sale of the services.
